{"name": "zipfile36", "metadata": {"name": "zipfile36", "version": "0.1.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Python Software Foundation License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: System :: Archiving :: Compression"], "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/takluyver/zipfile36", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Read and write ZIP files - backport of the zipfile module from Python 3.6", "upload_time": 1476623339}, "documentation": ["This is a backport of the zipfile module from Python 3.6, which contains some\nimprovements.\n\nInstallation:\n\n```\npip install zipfile36\n```\n\nSuggested usage:\n\n```python\nif sys.version_info >= (3, 6):\n    import zipfile\nelse:\n    import zipfile36 as zipfile\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "zipfile36", "documentation": ["Read and write ZIP files - backport of the zipfile module from Python 3.6"], "functions": [{"name": "zipfile36._check_zipfile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fp", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zipfile36.is_zipfile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Quickly see if a file is a ZIP file by checking the magic number.\n\nThe filename argument may be a file or file-like object too."]}, {"name": "zipfile36._EndRecData64", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fpin", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "offset", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "endrec", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Read the ZIP64 end-of-archive records and use that to update endrec"]}, {"name": "zipfile36._EndRecData", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fpin", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return data from the \"End of Central Directory\" record, or None.\n\nThe data is a list of the nine items in the ZIP \"End of central dir\"\nrecor